n"><span class="underline_span">Five-Part Rondo</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/sonataRondo"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Sonata Rondo</span></span></a></dd></dl></li><li class="nav_section"><dl><dt class="nav_header">Other formal structures in the classical style</dt> <dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/minuet"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Minuet form</span></span></a></dd></dl></li><li class="nav_section"><dl><dt class="nav_header">Galant Schemata</dt> <dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/schemataOpensAndCloses"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Galant schemata – opens and closes</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/schemataContinuationPatterns"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Galant Schemata – continuation patterns</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/schemataSummary"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Galant schemata – summary</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/schemata-improv"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Improvising a sentence with galant schemata</span></span></a></dd></dl></li><li class="nav_section"><dl><dt class="nav_header">(Post-tonal) Basics</dt> <dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/pitch-class"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Pitch (class)</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/interval-class"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Interval (class).</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/mod12"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Modular 12 arithmetic</span></span></a></dd></dl></li><li class="nav_section"><dl><dt class="nav_header">(Post-tonal) Organizing Forces</dt> <dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/scales2"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Collections and Scales</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/symmetryAndCentricity"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Symmetry and Centricity</span></span></a></dd></dl></li><li class="nav_section"><dl><dt class="nav_header">(Post-tonal) Set Theory</dt> <dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/normalOrder"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Normal Order</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/transposition"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Tranposition</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/inversion"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Inversion</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/setClassAndPrimeForm1"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Set Class and Prime Form (1)</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/setClassAndPrimeForm2"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Set Class and Prime Form (2)</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/complements"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Complements</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/commonTonesUnderTransposition"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Common Tones under Transposition</span></span></a></dd></dl></li><li class="nav_section"><dl><dt class="nav_header">(Post-tonal) 12-Tone Theory</dt> <dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/twelveToneBasics"><span class="hitbox_span"><span class="underline_span">Basics</span></span></a></dd><dd class="nav_item"><a href="/openmusictheory_reskinned/twelveToneOperations"><s